* Trump's policy and behavior is negatively impacting the real economy * Negative wealth effect lies ahead in light of markets decline From the September high, the S&P Index is now down by over 500 handles and 360 handles lower than when I wrote my 15 Surprises for 2019

in late November. Much of the decline lies at the foot of the policy and behavior of the President -- rather than Fed policy/comments. The number of cabinet members and senior White House officials that have left in dismay (Mattis) or disrepute is unprecedented.

Increasingly Trump's isolated nature, embracing of strong arm world leaders (at the expense of our allies), inexperience and lack of coherent and coordinated policies are making market participants uneasy. Stated simply, it looks like the U.S. government has no idea what it

is doing. It is unguided, led by Trump, and, seemingly, his daughter and son in law. This is a deeply serious situation in a flat and interconnected world. Reducing the capital gains tax is meaningless when no one has capital gains, and his tax package reduced the value of
capital losses! The next problem facing the markets and the domestic economy -- assuming a continuation of lower stock prices -- will be the negative wealth effect. Merry Christmas, Mr. President.
